   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>OUTLINE TWO SPEAKING POEMS</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>IN THE CHURCH MEETINGS</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>FOR THE ORGANIC BUILDING UP</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OF THE CHURCH AS THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Eph 5:18-19; Col 3:16; 1 Cor 14:23a, 26; Heb 10:24-25 The characteristics of proper poems: They are written according to the divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>They are written to express genuine spiritual experiences.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Through our speaking they dispense the divine life and illuminate with the divine light.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>They are the cream of a person s: Spiritual experience.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Learning.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Thought.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Utterance.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Writing.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To speak the composed, poetic writings is more accurate, concise, and powerful than ordinary speaking.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>When we speak the hymns one to another with the exercise of our spirit, Every sentence uttered by us touches the being of others.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Every sentence we speak ministers Christ into others being.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>It does not build up a congregation, but it builds up the organic Body of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The issue of speaking psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs in mutuality, one to another, in the church meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The word of Christ is ministered Col 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The Spirit is dispensed Eph 5:18-19.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Body of Christ is built up 1 Cor 14:26.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Teaching and admonishing are realized Col 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Exhortation results Heb 10:25.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Truths for enlightenment are revealed.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Life for supply is imparted.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Experiences of the Triune God are unveiled.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>God is manifested.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>By speaking poems in the church meetings, the meetings will be uplifted, strengthened, supplied, enriched, enlivened, and refreshed.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The speaking of the hymns works best in the group meetings with a smaller number Heb 10:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>However, we should learn and practice speaking the hymns in the larger meetings of the church for the mutual edification of the saints and the building up of the church 1 Cor 14:23a, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>In every church meeting it is good and profitable to use a proper hymn in a living way.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Necessary points to care for in speaking psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Exercise to have your whole being in full harmony with the Lord: A sober, clear mind.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>A calm emotion.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>An exercised spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>A heart free from all condemnation.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Overcome the two things that damage the meetings and the Lord s recovery: Our face.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Our pride.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Speak out of the enjoyment of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Speak to dispense God into people.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Release your spirit our spirit must be open, strong, real, genuine, and released, not weak, timid, false, or closed.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Be living and impressive in your speaking.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Speak to impress people with the points of the hymn.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Digest the portion spoken thoroughly.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Speak without anything religious or natural.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Speak without any routine, without anything traditional, and without any oldness.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Speak in a living and flowing manner with flexibility.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>A river flows straight and crooked, fast and slow, gentle and rough, and quiet and loud.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>In developing our exercise in speaking to one another in psalms, hymns and spiritual songs: We must be poor in spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>We must have a learning attitude.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>We must be sincere in our exercise.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>We will spontaneously adjust our practice as we corporately exercise ourselves in the speaking of the poems.</S>
   </TEXT>
